They didn’t apologize, take my name, or offer to refund my current order! 😡 It was very presumptuous of them to think I would ever call back and order again!  Nope, not happening. The food was good overall. All I got was a slice of pizza, a side of fries, and a 2 pcs. chocolate chip cookie dessert. The pizza was cold, but still yummy, the fries were okay at best, and the chocolate chip cookies were amazing. The prices are a bit more than what I'm used to spending for similar orders at other pizza/sub places, and honestly didn't seem completely worth it considering the fact that the pizza was actually cold and the side order of fries was kind of tiny compared to what I'm used to getting at other places. The staff were friendly and nice though, which is an important factor when deciding on a place to eat.. at least if you're eating there, because nobody likes rude or snobby seeming people regardless of where they are or what they're doing. They have a bathroom, but I'm not sure if it's actually supposed to be public as you have to go through an employee only door and go down to the basement in order to use it, if it isn't actually a public restroom then it was kind of the staff to let us use it. Overall I probably wouldn't choose this place on my own to go to, or revisit.. but it's one of my friend's favorite places to grab some quick and casual food to eat.

Always a go to when I need something quick and delicious. Quality meats and veggies for subs. Reliable pizza, even if the crust leaves something to be desired. The sauce and toppings are choice. Still haven't tried everything but plan to. They even got ice cream I want to try. It all looks amazing and the staff is super friendly. Within walking distance for me, so another reason I love it. Can't recommend enough!

I wouldn't even give it 1 star if it was up to me. I've worked there since Joe Bucceire and Carmine reopened it and it was a family  oriented restaurant. The customer's knew all our names and we knew all of theirs and their orders. We took pride in our food, our homemade sauce, Freshly pounded breaded cutlets, veal,eggplant and especially what we served to our customers.  Over the past 10 yrs it changed hands three times. Each time making changes some for the better some for the worst. We were always known for having the best food,best quality and best prices. As of last Friday, and im sure before that we were known for  bad customer service, giving customers wrong products, not for filling orders from grubhub,uber eats, slice. The prices went up , the food quality  and the genuine relationships between employees and customers were gone.  Very sad

Best food in Everett.. Until they sold it the other day.. It went from the best to awful. Im not about nasty reviews, so pay attention. They said delivery upwards of an hour. I was okay with that. The girl took my card number down, like always.. After an hour, they called me to tell me she lost it. So the second time, she wrote it down wrong. Calls back after an hour and 20 minutes to ask me again. Well, the foods obviously gonna arrive cold whenever it gets here. Ten minutes later, it arrived cold, but it wasn't the delivery guys fault. I gave him the right card number, and figured the owner would say don't charge it.. Nope, that was the old owners. They had class. Don't expect any such thing anymore. They no longer sell steak tips, the girl said cause meat is so expensive they'd have to charge $20 a plate. That says it all! I don't want cheap meat, and if I'm calling Buccis, I'm not worried about pinching pennies. It deeply saddens me to say this, it reallyyyyy does.. But go somewhere else.

This is my favorite spot to grab something to eat in Everett. They have everything you could want. They have pizza, all sorts of pasta dishes, an assortment of HOMEMADE Arancini (the traditional is my favorite), so many options for hot and cold subs (try the imported Italian, chicken cutlet club, or the Inception), & so much more! Don't expect lovey-dovey service all the time as this is as Everett as it comes, but it's undoubtedly one of those places where they truly love and take care of their customers. Hours are more limited than other takeout and delivery spots, and they're closed on Sunday. Don't forget to check out their catering options as well!
